    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: Your article ''Under the Arizona Sun'' (April 23) mentioned Will Tsosie, a Navajo who runs cultural tours in the Canyon de Chelly area. His counterpart on the Hopi reservation is Gary Tso, who can be reached at (520) 734-2567 or Left-Handed Hunter Tour Company, Post Office Box 434, Second Mesa, Ariz. 86043.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: Your article ''Under the Arizona Sun'' (April 23) mentioned Will Tsosie, a Navajo who runs cultural tours in the Canyon de Chelly area. His counterpart on the Hopi reservation is Gary Tso, who can be reached at (520) 734-2567 or Left-Handed Hunter Tour Company, Post Office Box 434, Second Mesa, Ariz. 86043.</p>
        <p>Taking cultural tours with Will and Gary was the highlight of our recent three-week tour of the Four Corners area. The fascination of our tours with these two cultural interpreters is that the Hopi and Navajo peoples have so much in common, so much intertwined history, yet are also so fundamentally different.</p>
        <p>CHUCK LUDLAM  Washington</p>
      </block>
